- `nuw` ensures truncated bits are zero (value fits in unsigned range)
- `nsw` ensures truncated bits match sign bit (value fits in signed range)  
- For unsigned comparison, we need to know value fits in unsigned range, which `nuw` on one operand provides
- The other operand having `nsw` doesn't guarantee it fits in unsigned range for comparison purposes

The transformation should be allowed if at least one operand has `nuw` for unsigned comparisons, not requiring both to have the same flag type.

